# Package Manager

This project uses **Bun** as the package manager and runtime. Always use `bun` instead of `npm`, `yarn`, or `pnpm`.

## Environment Setup

If bun is not available in the environment, install it globally:

```bash
npm install -g bun
```

Then install project dependencies:

```bash
bun install
```

**Important**: Do NOT use `package-lock.json`. This project uses `bun.lock` exclusively.

## Command Reference

| Instead of          | Use                            |
| ------------------- | ------------------------------ |
| `npm install`       | `bun install`                  |
| `npm install <pkg>` | `bun add <pkg>`                |
| `npm install -D`    | `bun add -d <pkg>`             |
| `npm run <script>`  | `bun run <script>`             |
| `npm test`          | `bun test`                     |
| `npm ci`            | `bun install --frozen-lockfile`|
| `npx <cmd>`         | `bunx <cmd>`                   |

## Examples

```bash
# Install dependencies
bun install

# Add a new dependency
bun add react-query

# Add a dev dependency
bun add -d vitest

# Run scripts
bun run dev
bun run build
bun run typecheck

# Execute a package binary
bunx wrangler deploy

# Format code (always run before finishing a task)
bun run format

# Run all checks
bun run typecheck && bun run lint
```
